<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/2049: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Sweden (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-03T20:00:00-04:00">March 3,
                                    1942—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>121. The Department’s approval of the plans to which you refer for the
                            relief of Greece has been made known to the British Government. You are
                            consequently requested to associate yourself with the British Minister
                            in the necessary discussions with the Swedish Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>